<div class="content">
  <div class="span-8">
    <p>I take full responsibility for the design and code of this website. It is built using <a href="http://docpad.org">DocPad</a>, a powerful static site generator written in <a href="http://nodejs.org">Node</a>. DocPad offers a robust <a href="http://docpad.org/docs/plugins">plugin ecosystem</a> with support for templates, partials and CSS compilers. Out of this wide universe, thegreatsunra.com uses <a href="https://github.com/sstephenson/eco">Eco</a> CoffeeScript templates, <a href="http://sass-lang.com/">Sass</a> and <a href="http://compass-style.org/">Compass</a> to get the job done.</p>
    <p>Before DocPad, this site was built in <a href="http://get-serve.com/">Serve</a>, an awesome Ruby gem with a lightweight development server, ERB templates, Compass integration and static exports. Before that it used <a href="https://github.com/EllisLab/CodeIgniter/">CodeIgniter</a>, a PHP-based MVC framework.</p>
    <p>The grid-based layout of this site uses a lightweight CSS framework <a href="https://gist.github.com/thegreatsunra/6379121">of my own devising</a>, inspired by <a href="http://blueprintcss.org/">Blueprint CSS</a>, <a href="http://960.gs/">960.gs</a> and <a href="http://html5boilerplate.com/">HTML5 Boilerplate</a>.
    <p>I use a mid-2012 13&rdquo; MacBook Air. I write all my code in <a href="http://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text</a> and host it in Git repositories at <a href="http://github.com/thegreatsunra">GitHub</a>. On the days I need FTP, I use Panic&rsquo;s <a href="http://panic.com/transmit/">Transmit</a>. I maintain a local development environment using <a href="http://nodejs.org">Node</a> for just about anything, and <a href="https://rvm.io">RVM</a> and <a href="http://www.mamp.info/en/mamp-pro/index.html">MAMP PRO</a> for everything else.</p>
    <p>I try to keep my life organized in <a href="http://evernote.com/">Evernote</a> and <a href="http://culturedcode.com/things/">Things</a>, but honestly it&rsquo;s unread email that make the world turn.</p>
    <p><em>&mdash; Last updated: November, 2013</em>
